title: Symmetrischema dulce
data: Symmetrischema dulce, the pepper-fruit-borer, is a moth in the family Gelechiidae. It was described by Povoln√Ω in 1984. It is found in Brazil.[1] The larvae feed on Capsicum frutescens.[2] This article on a moth of the tribe Gnorimoschemini is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.
